'''NGC 1964'''是位於[[天兔座|天兔座]]的[[棒旋星系|棒旋星系]]，距離地球約6500萬光年。該星系盤面直徑約10萬光年，並且中心的[[超重黑洞|超重黑洞]]質量約為2.5 × 10<sup>7</sup> {{solar mass|link=y}}<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Davis|first1=Benjamin L.|last2=Berrier|first2=Joel C.|last3=Johns|first3=Lucas|last4=Shields|first4=Douglas W.|last5=Hartley|first5=Matthew T.|last6=Kennefick|first6=Daniel|last7=Kennefick|first7=Julia|last8=Seigar|first8=Marc S.|last9=Lacy|first9=Claud H. S.|title=THE BLACK HOLE MASS FUNCTION DERIVED FROM LOCAL SPIRAL GALAXIES|journal=The Astrophysical Journal|date=20 June 2014|volume=789|issue=2|pages=124|doi=10.1088/0004-637X/789/2/124|accessdate=16 May 2017|arxiv = 1405.5876 |bibcode = 2014ApJ...789..124D }}</ref>。NGC 1964有兩個位於高表面亮度的盤面內的緊密纏繞的內側旋臂，另有兩個發源自內側環結構附近，結構較鬆散的外側旋臂。而外側旋臂有少許小範圍的[[电离氢区|H II區]]存在<ref>{{cite book|last1=Sandage|first1=A.|last2=Bedke|first2=J.|title=The Carnegie Atlas of Galaxies. Volume I|date=1994|publisher=Carnegie Institution of Washington|url=http://ned.ipac.caltech.edu/cgi-bin/datasearch?search_type=Note_id&objid=12574&objname=NGC%201964&img_stamp=YES&hconst=73.0&omegam=0.27&omegav=0.73&corr_z=1&of=table|access-date=2017-10-13|archive-date=2019-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207165325/http://ned.ipac.caltech.edu/cgi-bin/datasearch?search_type=Note_id&objid=12574&objname=NGC%201964&img_stamp=YES&hconst=73.0&omegam=0.27&omegav=0.73&corr_z=1&of=table|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

NGC 1964是NGC 1964星系群的主要成員星系，該星系群還包含了[[NGC_1979|NGC 1979]]、{{link-bs|IC 2130|IC 2130}}和{{link-bs|IC 2137|IC 2137}}<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Makarov|first1=Dmitry|last2=Karachentsev|first2=Igor|title=Galaxy groups and clouds in the local (z∼ 0.01) Universe|journal=Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society|date=21 April 2011|volume=412|issue=4|pages=2498–2520|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2966.2010.18071.x|url=http://www.sao.ru/hq/dim/groups/galaxies.dat|bibcode=2011MNRAS.412.2498M|arxiv=1011.6277|access-date=2017-10-13|archive-date=2016-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131020344/http://www.sao.ru/hq/dim/groups/galaxies.dat|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

